<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hover" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hover,</orth> 1) to hang in the air overhead or about: <bibl n="shak. lc 319" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 319</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 2, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 103</bibl>.<lb />2) to be irresolute, to waver: <cit><quote>--ing o'er the paper with her quill,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1297" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1297</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a --ing temporizer,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.302" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 302</bibl></cit>.
